import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Count the occurrences of each business category
    category_counts = data['key'].value_counts()

    # Create a bar chart of business categories
    plt.bar(category_counts.index, category_counts.values)
    plt.xlabel('Business Category')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Businesses')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of business categories in the University District area?', wrap=True)

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    scatter = ax.scatter(data['lat'], data['key'], c=data['key'].cat.codes, cmap='viridis', label=data['key'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Latitude')
    ax.set_ylabel('Business Category')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of business locations in the University District area?', wrap=True)
    legend1 = ax.legend(*scatter.legend_elements(), title="Categories")
    ax.add_artist(legend1)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Calculate the distances between businesses
    data['lat_shifted'] = data['lat'].shift(-1)
    data['distance'] = np.abs(data['lat'] - data['lat_shifted'])
    data = data.dropna()

    # Plot the histogram of distances between businesses
    plt.hist(data['distance'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Distances')
    plt.axvline(data['distance'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Average: {data['distance'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Distance')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the average distance between businesses in the University District area?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    data.boxplot(column='lat', by='key', ax=ax)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of business ratings in the University District area?')
    plt.suptitle('')
    plt.xlabel('Business Category')
    plt.ylabel('Latitude')
    plt.legend(title='Business Categories', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
